Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Public Defender Order Appointing Counsel - Atty Herbers
To Seal Victim/Witness Identification Key, Signed by Judge Jennifer R. Dorow on September 15th, 2022.

Defendant to comply with I.D. Processing.  Defendant to have no contact with victims/witnesses/the hotel listed in the Criminal Complaint/Victim Identification Key.  Defendant is not to share, reproduce or distribute any personal and/or identifying information about the crime victim(s), except to their attorney.  Absolute sobriety, defendant is not to possess or consume any alcohol. Defendant is not to use/possess any controlled substances without a valid prescription and take as prescribed.  Defendant not to possess any drug paraphernalia.  Defendant to report/comply with Wisconsin Community Services Pretrial Supervision Program under Level 2 supervision.  The defendant is ordered to comply with CAM monitoring and/or drug testing through WCS.  CAM duration and/or drug testing frequency pursuant to Pretrial Supervision Program protocols. Defendant to pay costs associated with CAM and/or drug testing.  Defendant to report to WCS the first business day after their release from custody.

1:21 PM Defendant Rebecca L Llanas in court, in custody. Attorney Luis Daniel Gutierrez in court for Rebecca L Llanas. District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin by Julian Marruto.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed. Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint and waives reading of complaint. Service admitted/advised of charges and potential penalties. NOT GUILTY PLEA ENTERED.  The Court sets this matter for further proceedings and will further remove the pre-trial date currently scheduled on case 22CM913 and set the two matters together before Judge Jennifer Dorow.  
Hearing scheduled for November 8, 2022 at 11:00 am.
Victim/Witness Identification Key filed, under seal, by the District Attorney's office.
